engage in external practices. The only worthwhile measure of spiritual prog=
ress and purity is how smaller your ego becomes. As ego
 becomes smaller, y=
ou can resist attraction to external things better and you can resist inter=
nal enemies like lust, anger, jealosy etc better. You can do your dharma be=
tter. Ego - thinking that this is "I" and this is "mine" - is the root caus=
